  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "dhcp security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for dhcp is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "The Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP) is a network management protocol used on UDP/IP networks whereby a DHCP server dynamically assigns an IP address and other network configuration parameters to each device on a network so they can communicate with other IP networks.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nBIND resolvers are vulnerable to an amplified resource consumption/exhaustion attack.  If a victim resolver makes a query to a specially crafted zone, the resolver will consume disproportionate resources.\nThis issue affects BIND 9 versions 9.11.0 through 9.16.50, 9.18.0 through 9.18.48, 9.20.0 through 9.20.22, 9.21.0 through 9.21.21, 9.11.3-S1 through 9.16.50-S1, 9.18.11-S1 through 9.18.48-S1, and 9.20.9-S1 through 9.20.22-S1.(CVE-2026-3592)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for dhcp is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "dhcp",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
